ymenu - dynamic yuki menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.
ymenu is an fork of dmenu courtesy of YukiNFan2002 !
Patching is done by YukiFan2002 !

Requirements
------------
In order to build ymenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (ymenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install ymenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running ymenu
-------------
See the man page for details.


Ymenu changes
-------------
-Added alpha patch, required extra flag in config.mk
-Added center patch
-Added border patch (5 by default)
-Changed font size and font to source code pro
-15 Lines (-l flag) by default
-Patched in fuzzy match
-Rebinded the Mod1+h/j/k/l keys to be more comfy/vim-like
(Mod1+h pages up, Mod+l pages down, Mod1+j moves down, Mod1+k moves up) 
